.TH IFONT2H 1 "June 2026" "ilib @ILIB_VERSION@" "Ilib Manual"
.SH NAME
ifont2h \- convert an X11 BDF font to a C header
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ifont2h
.I font.bdf
.B >
.I font.h
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ifont2h
reads an X11 BDF font file and writes a C header to standard output. The
header defines a
.B "char *<name>_font[]"
array (where
.I <name>
is the base name of the input file with its extension removed) holding the
font data, wrapped in an include guard.
.PP
Compiling that header into a program and passing the array to
.B ILoadFontFromData()
lets the program draw text with the font without needing the
.B .bdf
file at runtime. This is how the bundled
.BR isample (1)
and other clients embed their fonts.
.PP
.B COMMENT
lines in the BDF file are skipped. Unlike the other Ilib tools,
.B ifont2h
does not link against the Ilib library.
.SH EXAMPLES
Embed the Helvetica 24 font shipped with Ilib:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ifont2h /usr/local/share/ilib/fonts/helvR24.bdf > helvR24.h
.fi
.RE
.PP
then in your program:
.PP
.RS
.nf
#include "helvR24.h"
IFont font;
ILoadFontFromData("helvR24", helvR24_font, &font);
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, or 1 if no file was given or it could not be opened.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR idisplayfont (1),
.BR isample (1)
.PP
Full API documentation: https://craigk5n.github.io/ilib/
